         <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
            <div type="textpart" n="in fastigio">
               <ab><lb n="1"/><lg met="choliambic">
                  <l n="1" met="choliamb" real="++-+-++--+-++--++">
                     
                     <supplied reason="lost">Si</supplied>
                     <supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">q</supplied>
                     <unclear>u</unclear>a tamen pietas gelidos movet <unclear>r</unclear>u<unclear>stic</unclear>a M<supplied reason="lost" source="CLE" evidence="previouseditor">anes</supplied>,</l>
                  <l n="2" met="choliamb" real="+--+++-+--+--++">
                     <lb n="2"/>rumpe moras <supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="CLE">spes haec s</supplied>ola est mihi gratia <supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="CLE">vitae</supplied>.</l>
               </lg></ab>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" n="in fronte">
               <ab>
                  <lb n="1"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="praenomen" key="Marcus">
                        <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arco</ex></expan>
                     </name>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Iunius">Iunio</name>
                     <persName>
                        <name type="praenomen" key="Marcus">
                           <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan>
                        </name>
                     </persName>
                     <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan>
                     <expan><abbr>Pal</abbr><ex>atinatribu</ex></expan>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Rufus">Rufo</name>
                  </persName>
                  <lb n="2"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Soterichus">Soterichus</name>
                  </persName>
                  <expan><abbr>paedagog</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> fecit.
                        <lb n="3"/>Hae sunt parvae tuae <expan><abbr>meaeq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> sedes,
                        <lb n="4"/>haec certa est domus, haec colenda nobis,
                        <lb n="5"/>haec est quem mihi suscitavi vivus.
                    </ab>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>in fastigio</p>
            <p>But if a rustic piety moves, somehow, those cold Spirits—end this wait—this hope is, to me, life’s one grace.</p>
            <p>in fronte</p>
            <p>To Marcus Junius Rufus, son of Marcus, from the Palatine (tribe); Soterichus, (his) <hi rend="italic">paedagogus</hi> , made (this for him); this little thing is the resting place of you and me, this is our fixed dwelling, to be protected by us, this is what I—living—built up for myself.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>There are new pieces set on top. The base is modern and has been removed. The
                    front of the bottom is modern as well (The Walters Art Museum).</p>
         </div>
